  "prompt": "Men's Health: What is stress?",
  "response": "Stress is the body's physical, mental, and emotional response to challenging or demanding situations. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n1. Definition\n- A natural human reaction to pressure or challenges\n- Body's automatic defense mechanism\n- Can be short-term or long-term\n\n2. Types of Stress\n- Acute stress (short-term)\n- Chronic stress (long-term)\n- Positive stress (motivating)\n- Negative stress (harmful)\n\n3. Physical Symptoms\n- Increased heart rate\n- Elevated blood pressure\n- Muscle tension\n- Headaches\n- Fatigue\n- Sleep disturbances\n\n4. Psychological Symptoms\n- Anxiety\n- Depression\n- Irritability\n- Difficulty concentrating\n- Mood swings\n\n5. Common Causes\n- Work pressure\n- Financial problems\n- Relationship issues\n- Health concerns\n- Major life changes\n- Traumatic experiences\n\n6. Potential Health Consequences\n- Weakened immune system\n- Cardiovascular problems\n- Digestive issues\n- Mental health disorders\n- Increased risk of chronic diseases\n\n7. Stress Management Techniques\n- Regular exercise\n- Meditation\n- Adequate sleep\n- Healthy diet\n- Time management\n- Counseling/therapy\n\nUnderstanding and managing stress is crucial for overall men's health and well-being.",
